# Publishing to PyPI

CRITICAL: Always build from the PUBLIC repo (jbdel/RadEval), never from hopprai/RadEval.
The private repo contains proprietary metrics that must not appear on PyPI.

## Full workflow

```bash
# 1. Push latest to hopprai/RadEval (private)
cd /fss/jb/RadEval
git push origin main

# 2. Publish to jbdel/RadEval (public, strips private metrics)
python scripts/publish_public.py --push

# 3. Clone the PUBLIC repo into a temp dir and build from there
cd /tmp
git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/jbdel/RadEval.git radeval_pypi
cd radeval_pypi
python -m build --sdist

# 4. Upload (token is in scripts/pypi, use __token__ as username)
TWINE_USERNAME=__token__ TWINE_PASSWORD="<token from scripts/pypi>" twine upload dist/*

# 5. Clean up
rm -rf /tmp/radeval_pypi
```

## Version bumping

Before uploading, bump the version in `setup.py` (line `version='...'`).
PyPI rejects duplicate versions, so every upload must have a new version string.

## Dependencies

Ensure `twine` and `build` are installed: `pip install twine build`

## The scripts/pypi file

Contains the PyPI API token. It is NOT a script to execute directly.
Read the token from it and pass it as TWINE_PASSWORD.
